programmes.show_description: Poutine, Pizza And Pork. Guy is on the hunt for some meaty masterpieces! He checks out a poutine burger in Colorado, potato chip pie in Texas and killer clay-pot chicken in Arizona. S27, Ep11
Belly Up To Barcelona. Guy Fieri crosses the Atlantic to take a bite out of Barcelona! He visits a homely spot serving Galician-style octopus and tries old-school Catalan food. S26, Ep1
A Sampling Of Spain. Guy Fieri is in Barcelona for a gastronomic feast! He tries out dishes from prawn and quail tapas, to traditional Catalan specialties including veal-head stew. S26, Ep2
Mega Mouthfuls. Guy Fieri unhinges his jaw for some mega-mouthful meals. In Louisville, KY, a seafood spot piles their specialities on top of waffles and he visits a BBQ food truck. S26, Ep3
Long Island. Adam Richman is on Long Island, New York, for a massive plate of Italian food, a colossal gelato sundae and the Davey Jones' Locker Challenge. S2, Ep28
Oklahoma City. Adam Richman is in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma, for a presidential T-bone steak, the Sooner State original fried onion burger and a Fried Catfish Challenge. S2, Ep29
Roses, Romance, & A Romeo. Buddy has his work cut out when he's asked to make wedding cakes for fourteen couples getting hitched in a mass wedding ceremony on Valentine's Day. S3, Ep4
Hieroglyphics, Hearse, & Happy Parents. Buddy and the team make three uniquely outrageous cakes including a pink hearse cake, a baby shower cake and an Egyptian-themed sweet 16 cake. S3, Ep5

On The Hook And In The Bun. Guy reels in yummy seafood and serious sandwiches. He checks out a fresh poke burger on Hawaii and pork buns and dim sum chicken feet in San Francisco. S28, Ep15
Culinary Journey. Guy Fieri's culinary journey includes a Filipino-Hawaiian fusion in Hawaii that leaves diners speechless. And, a Spanish eatery in Chicago serves top seafood. S28, Ep19
Ocean Coasts And Great Lakes. Guy Fieri seeks out dynamite dishes from the coasts to the Great Lakes. He discovers outrageous octopus tostadas and gourmet grilled cheese sandwiches. S27, Ep4
Sammies And Spice. Guy Fieri hunts down standout sandwiches. He tries a primo pork burger in Longmont, CO, and some serious spice with fiery Thai specialties in Los Angeles. S27, Ep8
Cooking With Wine. Ina Garten reveals the secrets of cooking with wine and gets tips on cheese and wine pairings. Recipes include beef short ribs and raspberry gratins. S3, Ep3
Cooking For Beginners. Ina gets a tagine cooking lesson from teacher and private chef Gail Arnold. Her beginners' recipe includes meat loaf, preserved lemons and roasted asparagus. S3, Ep4
Perfect French Dinner Party. Ina Garten creates the perfect French dinner party inspired by her trips to France. The menu features a slow-cooked lamb and Provencal French beans. S3, Ep5
All About Chocolate. Ina Garten goes chocolate-mad, with secrets from chocolatier Brigitte Browney. Recipes include tiered chocolate buttercream cake, and rum raisin truffles. S3, Ep6
Cooking With Rice. Ina Garten shares incredible recipes for sweet and savoury rice dishes. Her delicious menu includes shrimp and sausage jambalaya to maple pecan rice pudding. S3, Ep7
High Wire Egg Dishes. Ina Garten tackles the trickiest egg recipes! She has an omelette masterclass with local chef Terry Harwood and reveals the secret to a perfect souffle. S3, Ep8
Classics With A Twist. Nadiya Hussain presents her recipes for classic bakes with a twist. Cupcakes given an ice cream-flavour and the classic scone is given an update. S1, Ep1
Indulgent Desserts. Nadiya Hussain turns her attention to desserts. Nadiya starts off with a frozen, vegan no-cheese cheesecake with banana and blueberries. S1, Ep2
Savoury Bakes. Nadiya Hussain shares her savoury baking recipe, including her chicken and pink peppercorn pithivier that has a whole brie hidden inside. S1, Ep3
Baking With Chocolate. Nadiya Hussain shares four recipes that make the most of chocolate. To begin with, Nadiya makes her 'Money Can't Buy You Happiness Brownie'. S1, Ep4
James travels to Bresse, a region in France he's never visited before. He visits a chicken farm and museum and meets one of his culinary heroes, George Blanc. S1, Ep9
James travels to a region known for its Pinot Noir, Burgundy. He retraces Keith Floyd's visits 30 years ago and stops at the same vineyard for a personal tour. S1, Ep10
Feasts. Dame Mary Berry journeys to some of the places closest to her heart. She recalls memories from her past and creates new ones, sharing delicious new recipes. S1, Ep5
Crowd Pleasers. Mary heads to Edinburgh and meets the runners at the city's marathon. Her hearty treats include chocolate rocky road and eggy bread avocado and ham sandwiches. S1, Ep6
Delicious Memories. Mary travels to Scotland to enjoy recipes inspired by her own Scots heritage. And, she shares the joys of venison cooked on a barbecue. S1, Ep1
Hearty And Wholesome. Mary shares inspiring dishes full of wholesome goodness. She tries her hand at beekeeping, collecting fresh honey to make a delicious pudding. S1, Ep2
Big Crowd Pleasers. Mary hosts a village fete and shows off her flair for turning simple dishes into spectacular crowd pleasers. And, she shares her recipe for an Italian pizza. S1, Ep3
Naughty But Nice. Mary makes mouth-watering meals with lashings of naughtiness, including an easy sticky toffee pudding. Plus, she pursues the history of the great British pie. S1, Ep4
Feeding The Family. Mary shares some inspirational ideas to make fabulous family meals. Plus, she shows her granddaughter how to make her own goat's cheese. S1, Ep5
When You Want To Show Off. Mary is pushing the boat out to celebrate her 50th wedding anniversary. She shares her secrets to surprisingly easy showstoppers. S1, Ep6
Polish Pizza Puzzle. Adam Richman finds secret eats in Warsaw, Poland. Dishes include a Polish spin on Neapolitan pizza, and a classic Polish street food known as a zapiekanka. S2, Ep13
Under The Radar Rome. Adam travels to Rome to uncover off-menu eats. Dishes include a unique take on Cacio e Pepe, traditional Porchetta, and an off-menu pasta dish. S2, Ep14
Turin. Adam is in Turin tasting the most iconic foods named after this city including an amazing breaded beef cutlet and a veal and tuna favourite. S1, Ep5
Genoa. Adam is in Genoa tasting the most iconic foods named after the city, including a pasta dish made with pesto Genovese and a fish stew called burrida. S1, Ep6
Funky Fresh. Guy Fieri's filling up on fresh pasta in Chicago, a banh mi smash burger in Montana and craveable Southern classics in Florida. S41, Ep1
Dallas, Florida And Chi-Tacos. Guy Fieri's digging into delicious dumplings in Dallas, gator sausage in Florida, and lights-out mojo pork with plantains in Chicago. S41, Ep2
Barbecue And Beer Can Chicken. Guy Fieri grabs some crazy grub! In Hawaii he finds a funky joint serving beer can chicken. Plus, he stops at a downtown barbecue spot in Los Angeles. S27, Ep3
From Pied To Fried. Guy Fieri scours the US for amazing food. He checks out ramen in St. Petersburg, FL and a funky joint frying up chicken gizzards in Lansing, MI. S27, Ep7
Swiss, Sandwiches And Sausage. Guy Fieri stops in Portland, OR, and Charlotte, NC, to sample grilled cheese sandwiches with a twist, schnitzel, sausage and Swiss specialities. S26, Ep4
Beef, Lamb And Pig. Guy Fieri hunts down meaty favourites in Kentucky and North Carolina. He enjoys an Irish pub's cottage pie, Asian-barbecue fusion and pimento-topped burgers. S26, Ep5

On The Hook And In The Bun. Guy reels in yummy seafood and serious sandwiches. He checks out a fresh poke burger on Hawaii and pork buns and dim sum chicken feet in San Francisco. S28, Ep15
Playin' Chicken. Guy plays a tasty game of chicken all over the US. He finds it Nashville hot-style in California and French-style at a pizza-pasta place in Seattle! S28, Ep14
Far East Flavorfest. Guy Fieri cruises the states to check out Far-Eastern flavours, from chicken with an Asian spin in Seattle and Thai in Hawaii to modern Korean wings in Chicago. S28, Ep18

Fusion Of Flavors. Guy digs into a range of flavour fusions, from a Latin-Asian mashup in Chicago with paella and posole to a Hawaiian spot serving guava ribs and tropical pizza. S28, Ep16
Sandwiches, Spaetzle And Wings. In Virginia, Guy Fieri finds a spot serving sandwiches by day and sticky wings at night. In Hawaii, a German-Swiss joint dishes up apple strudel. S27, Ep1
A Passport Of Flavor. Guy Fieri cruises from Texas to Michigan for cuisine with international flair, including shawarma, brisket banh mi, tequila croissants and old-school sourdough. S27, Ep5
College-Town Champs. Guy Fieri heads to college towns for top grade cuisine. In Columbus, OH, he finds a pierogi paradise and in Boulder, CO, a Thai joint serves knockout noodles. S27, Ep9
Hartford, Connecticut. Adam Richman is off to Hartford, Connecticut for some humongous hot dogs, steamed cheeseburgers, and a ten-pound super-stuffed pizza challenge. S2, Ep20
Salt Lake City. Adam Richman journeys to Salt Lake City, Utah, for a unique pastrami-topped cheeseburger, a Belgian sausage sandwich and a diabolically spicy Hellfire Challenge. S2, Ep22
Phoenix. Food fanatic Adam Richman visits Phoenix, Arizona, for a two-foot-long, fully loaded hot dog and the five-pound Ultimate Slider Challenge. S2, Ep24
Puerto Rico. Adam is in San Juan, Puerto Rico, sampling an enormous deep-fried pork chop, a churrasco steak sandwich and his biggest challenge yet: a nine-pound steak platter! S2, Ep26
Long Island. Adam Richman is on Long Island, New York, for a massive plate of Italian food, a colossal gelato sundae and the Davey Jones' Locker Challenge. S2, Ep28
San Diego. Adam Richman heads to San Diego, California, for a massive surf-and-turf burrito, tender tri-tip barbecue and a legendary Ironman food challenge. S2, Ep21
Cleveland. Adam Richman is in Cleveland, Ohio, for a Greek gyro bursting with savoury beef, the state's signature spicy sausage sandwich and a five-pound grilled cheese challenge. S2, Ep23
Boulder. Adam Richman takes his food quest to Boulder, Colorado, for mile-high pizza and bacon pancakes. Then, he takes on his biggest wing challenge yet! S2, Ep25

James indulges in the glitz and glamour of St. Tropez. He explores the local seafood market and, in true St. Tropez style, cooks his first dish aboard a yacht. S1, Ep11
James experiences the bustling Provencal port of Marseille. There he discovers local fishermen selling fresh seafood on the back of their boats. S1, Ep12
Semi-Final: Patisserie Week. The bakers show off their patisserie skills with a delicate domed signature dish and a showstopper that features its own edible display case. S10, Ep9
The Final. Paul and Prue set three challenges that test every aspect of the bakers' skills. After tackling a tough technical, the bakers must create a deceptive picnic basket feast. S10, Ep10
The bakers kick off Cake Week by putting their twist on Battenberg cake. They face a turning-out technical challenge and pay tribute to their heroes in the showstopper. S11, Ep1
In Biscuit Week, the bakers make a sophisticated fruit, nut and chocolate combination and tropical technical. Plus, there's an elaborate table setting showstopper. S11, Ep2
Guernsey. James and his mate Mark Jordan rev up their motorbikes to discover the delights of Guernsey. They sample the local speciality of Gache cake. S1, Ep5
Dorset. James's trip along the south coast continues in Dorset with pal and award-winning chef, Paul Ainsworth. They enjoy a gorgeous beachside barbeque. S1, Ep6
